      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "e90d29fa514e6d79",
      "text": "**Confusion and misunderstanding** result when communications sent at one level of language are received and interpreted at another. In the story Being There by Jerry Kosinski, Chance, the gardener, becomes Chauncey Gardiner and his utterances about the growing season, the weather and the seasons are interpreted as profound statements about the state of the economy and society.\n"
